    {
      "id": "custom-node-pattern-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Custom Node Pattern",
      "position": {
        "x": -120,
        "y": -120
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Custom Node Pattern\n\nThe goal is not to hide everything in React, and not to pretend a class script should render buttons. We want a clean graph-native path for custom nodes:\n\n- host renderer owns generic control rendering and dispatch\n- node class owns declared controls, views, state transitions, and scripts\n- custom nodes become authored artifacts instead of one-off React escapes",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
