    {
      "id": "custom-node-pattern-note-bootstrap",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Bootstrap Node Lesson",
      "position": {
        "x": 1560,
        "y": -200
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Bootstrap Node Lesson\n\nThe bootstrap handshake proved the right baseline:\n\n- node-specific surface and state live in the class file\n- generic copy/paste and event-reaction machinery live in the renderer\n- the node can look custom and behave custom without becoming a bespoke node type\n\nThat is the pattern to preserve.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
